    • Method Detail

      • estimateSize

        public static long estimateSize(DecisionTree<?> tree)
        Estimate the number of nodes in a tree. Currently this is a very basic implementation that just follows one path through the tree to a leaf and assumes that the size of the tree is the product of the choices at each visited node.
        Parameters:
        tree - The tree to size
        Returns:
        the estimated size of the tree

      • showHistory

        public static java.lang.String showHistory(DecisionTree<?> tree)
        Display the history of a given DecisionTree in a human readable format. This displays all of the decision points in the history of this point where there was more than one choice to be made.
        Parameters:
        tree - the tree to examine
        Returns:
        a human readable view of the history of decisions that lead to this tree
